This build starts out as an arcane missile clones build in the campaign, turns into a ray of obliteration clones build with the ferocious affinity reaper in the first and second adam nostrus trials, remains as a ray of obliteration clones build but with the ungifted reaper in the third adam nostrus trial and finally becomes a lightning imbued ray of obliteration clones build with the vengeance reaper in the end game.

This build does not use any legendary effects until the third adam nostrus trial. It is easy to swap to this build halfway before this.

You will be able to clear the game using the “ethical” part of the guide. The final build in the end game after full clearing the game is an “unethical” build. There are elitist players out there that deem builds using the vengeance reaper or going past \+15 reinforcement levels as unethical builds. They will look down on you for playing this. Try the unethical part at your own risk.

If you wish to play a “proper” dps build, play till the stop sign before it is turned into an unethical build.  
If you wish to play a “proper” magic find build, go for [Golden Overdrive]({% post_url blitzy/2025-05-14-G1B0000001 %}) instead.

## **Build details for the lightning imbued vengeance version**

Build design  
The original intention was to design a magic find build that can farm for slormites and pure stats grafting feed faster than simply farming in the forge. Even with extreme luck and super optimal reward options in the forge, there is a hard cap.  
Magic items quantity and magic items quality does not work in the forge. However, with unlimited reinforcement levels comes unlimited scaling, our drop-related stats will eventually exceed the amount of war chest quantity/quality and rewards that forge can offer. This is especially so when [there are new areas in the game that have higher enemies killed per second than the forge](https://discord.com/channels/531482023102251018/531482023102251022/1370921527016554506).  
The design is heavily focused on dishing out as many hits as possible in a huge area while staying as a low apm build. This is mainly because of how annoyed I was by the nullifying shield cataclysm. This build is designed to minimise the annoyance and time wasted by the nullifying shield cataclysm.  
This build is only meant for those who wish to pour unlimited hours into the game. If you want to try many builds you should stop at the stop sign below.

Vengeance reaper  
Infinite life and damage scaling. This reaper covers both survivability and damage which gives us space to fit in drop rate related stats and quality of life solutions into the build.

Build goals  
Unlimited scaling of Magic Items Quantity and Magic Items Quality for more and better drops.  
Unlimited scaling of damage to one shot monsters for faster clearing speed.  
High movement speed for faster clearing speed.  
100% Tenacity for unimpeded movement for faster clearing speed.  
Auto aim using clones for quality of life.  
Low apm skill for quality of life.  
Non-projectile skill which will not be impeded by projectile blocking shields and projectile speed cataclysm for your sanity and faster clearing speed.  
High range skill for faster clearing speed.  
High number of hits per second to minimise time wasted by the nullifying shield cataclysm for faster clearing speed.  
AOE hits for faster clearing speed.

Life  
We gain max life from the reaper, which can be scaled to infinity.

Life sustain  
We avoid using life leech and life regeneration to sustain life to avoid getting cucked by the cataclysms.  
Coward’s belt from our belt’s legendary effect will restore 5% of missing life every 3 seconds.  
Life sustain can be stopped by the shadow confusion debuff. We counter this by getting a capped 100% shadow resistance.

Skill Cost  
Ray of obliteration and electric overcharge originally cost mana to channel. We turn this into life using the crimson pact ring legendary effect so that our life sustain solution also solves our skill cost.

Damage  
We mainly deal elemental damage. Our source of elemental damage is the 4000 elemental damage granted by investing slorm into all ancestral legacy effects. We scale this 4000 elemental damage using our reaper, which can be scaled to infinity.

How we deal damage  
The first way to deal damage is through ray of obliteration clones. We can cast up to 2 clones (4 if you change specialisation for forge farming), 1 from the base limit and 1 additional clone limit from the arcane lord from our helmet’s legendary effect.  
The second way to deal damage is through electric arc. We imbue our ray of obliteration clones with lightning by allocating electric overcharge. This will cause our ray of obliteration clones to trigger an electric arc on hit. With static shock allocated, this triggered electric arc will hit up to 3 random nearby enemies. With the vambraces of polarity bracers legendary effect, this will allow electric arc to hit 4 random nearby enemies instead of 3 on the second hit and beyond.  
The third way to deal damage is through thunderbolt. With thunderstruck allocated, when our ray of obliteration clones deal an ancestral strike, it will trigger a thunderbolt on a random nearby enemy.  
The fourth way to deal damage is through walking bomb. With arming the bomb allocated, when our ray of obliteration clones deal an ancestral strike, it will apply walking bomb to the enemy. With the ancient blazingspark talisman from our amulet’s legendary effect, applying walking bomb to the enemy will also trigger a thunderbolt on the enemy dealing damage to them. When the enemy with walking bomb dies, it triggers an explosion dealing damage to all enemies in the scalable area and applying an unspreadable walking bomb to all enemies hit. This application of the unspreadable walking bomb to enemies will also trigger a thunderbolt on them dealing damage to them.

Ancestral Strike chance  
We will attempt to reach a 100% effective ancestral strike chance for a 100% trigger rate of ancestral strike effects (thunderbolt and walking bomb).  
This is achieved by stacking critical strike chance and ancestral strike chance stats on our gear, allocating 10 points to fury and zeal for 10% critical strike chance and 5% ancestral strike chance, equipping the ancestral command passive from the phlegmatic caster specialisation, and gaining critical strike chance multiplier from the muzzling gloves from our gloves’ legendary effect. We do not care about the downside of the muzzling gloves due to our infinite damage scaling.  
With the muzzling gloves, you will need to reach a total of 85% ancestral strike chance and 40% critical strike chance on your gear stats.  
We will get up to 15% critical strike chance from bravery but that is unreliable so we will not be counting that.

Drops  
We will graft max score pure magic items quantity and magic items quality stats to every piece of gear. This can be scaled to infinity with the unlimited reinforcement levels.  
We will prioritise magic items quantity first. This gives us more equipment drops for an easier time at farming for pure stats and more slormite drops to reinforce our gear. Magic items quality comes next, it will result in more common epic equipment drops in case the pure stat you are looking for only appears as an epic stat, as well as higher tier of slormite drops.  
We will allocate 75 points to bravery for extra goldus find, magic items quality, and most importantly slormite find which cannot be found anywhere else.

Clear Speed  
We will be using the movement speed ultimatum with the oloron’s ultimate enhancer legendary effect to reach a decently high 3.5 movement speed. You can also opt to craft movement speed stats instead of using the ultimatum.  
We will cap tenacity at 100% to be immune to all crowd control effects. The only movement speed impeding effect that we cannot avoid is the ice floor.  
We choose ray of obliteration clones as our primary skill as it has a long range, has instant and automated targeting, does continuous and rapid hits, is able to hit all enemies along its beam aoe, and has infinite duration. This leads to a comfortable and less tiring low apm playstyle where you only need to press 1 button per area to clear all enemies. Can’t grind to infinity if you or your hands burns out first.  
We will stack as many area of effect size stats as possible on our gear. This will scale the aoe of walking bomb, giving us a bigger explosion on death effect for bigger clearing aoe.  
We use the midos’ collectors’ bracers and sparkling boots of midos legendary effects to increase our collection radius. This cuts down on the time spent moving to collect loot.  
We will attempt to cap cooldown reduction at 75% and attack speed at 90%. This will increase how fast we place our clones down, which is a very minimal increase to our clearing speed. At higher reinforcement levels when we no longer need phlegmatic caster to cap our ancestral strike chance, we might swap back to the arcane commander specialisation for two more clones. Having high cdr and as will help us place down all 4 clones faster.  
We have two movement skills, time warp and twitching warp. I am very doubtful that we will even bother using these movement skills with our high movement speed, and even especially so if you are playing using a controller.

# Campaign

Pick the Mischievous Mage. You will be levelling from 1 to the end of the campaign using Arcane Missile as your primary skill, Ray of Obliteration as your secondary skill and Arcane Commander as your Specialisation.  
This build uses the ferocious affinity reaper. This reaper is the fixed first drop for mage. If you did not start the save as a mage you will not get this reaper as the first fixed drop. You can still get it as a random drop later. This is not the best reaper for the build, it is used for convenience as it is a decently strong reaper and lets you skip reaper farming. The best reaper for this build is the ungifted reaper.

## **Act 1 The Graveyard**

1. Open your inventory, on the left you will find the character stats. Click on Life Leech and Max Mana to highlight them. Go to the second tab and click on Raw Damage to highlight it. Doing so will highlight loot that drops. It will also affect the item filter that we unlock later on. Items that dropped with the selected stats will be highlighted, you can choose to only loot these highlighted gear to save time.  
2. Keep 1 piece of gear with life leech equipped, just 1 is enough, the gear’s level and value of life leech doesn’t matter. Wear whichever gear gives you more raw damage. You can use the character info’s average skill damage estimate to determine which is better. If the gear does not have raw damage, wear whichever gives more max mana.  
3. Open your inventory, go to the third tab on the right for attributes. Remove the first point from Willpower and add it to Toughness. Add points to Toughness until you reach Toughness 15\.  
4. Try to kite (walk around the enemy) when attacking, do not stand there and facetank.  
5. At level 3 you will unlock Ray of Obliteration which is automatically equipped in the secondary slot. Leave it there, we will not be using it, but it still needs to be equipped for it to gain mastery levels for later use.  
6. Upgrade Arcane Funding (Arcane Missile) to Rank 1\. This lets you ignore mana cost for the entire campaign\!  
7. Upgrade Conflux (Arcane Missile) to Rank 4\.  
8. Equip the Signet Ring of the Mcrippeds that Pedro gives. Use emergency healing to restore life if you have to. You can replace this ring with better rings when you find and equip a gear with life leech.  
9. Talk to Pr. Geranium in town after saving him. This allows our reaper to start gaining levels.  
10. During Mission 5, you will get a Staff of Ferocious Affinity. Equip this new staff. You will start getting random reaper drops after this. Talk to Pr. Geranium in town again for a free legendary amulet.  
11. Fully refund Conflux (Arcane Missile). Upgrade Remnants Wingman (Arcane Missile) to Rank 7\. You now have extra projectiles for better clear. These remnants can shotgun if you attack near the enemy.  
12. After unlocking Jemma, you can sell excess gear to her. Or just throw them on the ground, doesn't really matter.  
13. At level 10, you will unlock specialisations. Open your skills menu and click “Become Arcane Commander”. You will not be using the support skill, it is equipped to gain mastery levels to unlock upgrades.  
14. Upgrade Arcanic Delegation (Arcane Missile) to Rank 1\. You can now place a clone to attack for you. You only have 1 clone for now, you will get 2 more from your specialisation later.  
15. Upgrade Remnants Wingman (Arcane Missile) to Rank 10\.  
16. After saving Palstrang, you unlock Expeditions. Ignore this system for now and continue on the campaign.  
17. After saving Adam Nostrus, talk to him in town. You will receive your first Ancestral Stone. Allocate Air Conditioner, upgrade it to Rank 1 and turn it on.  
18. At level 16, you should have 15 points in Toughness. Add remaining points to Zeal for the rest of the campaign.  
19. Upgrade Mana Protection (Arcane Commander) to Rank 1\.  
20. Kill the Act 1 Boss. Highlight the remaining text for spoilers/tips: \*\*Whenever the boss goes invulnerable, you have to kill all the summons with the red aura below to end the invulnerability.\*\*  
21. After killing the Act 1 Boss, talk to Adam Nostrus for another Ancestral Stone. Allocate Raw Boost. Upgrade it to Rank 10 after you have capped Remnants Wingman.

This act has the most annoying mobs, especially the prisoner which blocks the first 3 hits. I highly suggest skipping killing enemies that aren’t required by the quest to save time. For example, if the quest requires you to clear breaches, you should only bother killing enemies spawned by the breaches and simply skip the rest of the enemies on the way. DO NOT SKIP ANY BREACH, it might be one that unlocks an NPC.

# Adam Nostrus’ Trials 1

After the campaign, you will unlock the quest board next to Almerolis that contains the Adam Nostrus’ Trials. You will be unlocking multiple important pieces of gear such as the 3 runes, movement speed ultimatum and the 7th Ancestral Stone. ## **Level 40 and normal gear**

Head to the Mage Academy at the bottom left of the town, you will be levelling here for a quick boost to transition into Ray of Obliteration, as well as to obtain and craft your first set of temporary mid game gear.  

{% include embed/youtube.html id="d2w-uy7W1ZA" %}

1. Upgrade Regenerative Strikes (Ancestral Legacy) to Rank 10\.  
2. Go to the mage academy mission 4, tick Match my level  
3. Enter, rush to the 3 chaos breaches and trigger them all. Place 3 clones and channel Ray of Obliteration to kill all enemies then use the leave expedition key to leave. If this is too hard you can trigger the chaos breaches one after another instead of all at once.  
4. Repeat this until your Ray of Obliteration reaches Mastery Level 10\. It is time to respec into Ray of Obliteration. Refer to the [slorm allocation sequence for this phase](#slorm-allocation-sequence-\(adam-nostrus’-trials-1\):).  
5. Repeat the above until level 40\. Continue swapping to gear with the highest raw damage while doing so. This will earn you a good amount of slorm and levels.  
6. Temporarily turn off hiding of normal, magic, rare and epic items  
   Repeat Temppo until you loot a full set of at least level 36 gear. Once done, turn the hiding of normal, magic, rare, epic and legendary items back on.  
   ![][image4]  
7. Go to the blacksmith Friedrich. It is time to start crafting. Craft the following on your level 36+ magic item. Remember that you can scroll down for more crafting options as well as lock stats you do not want rerolled. Craft the Normal and Defense Stats and % Mana Leech. Magic Stats is optional, do it if you have enough magic slormelines. You can merge fragments into slormeline at the blacksmith, but I highly recommend that you skip this and save the gold for later use.  
   Helmet: Max Mana, Armour, % Armour or Elemental Resistance  
   Amulet: % Raw Damage, Armour  
   Chest: Max Mana, Raw Damage, Armour  
   Cape: Max Mana, Armour  
   Belt: Raw Damage, Armour  
   Rings x2: % Raw Damage, Armour, Max Mana or Raw Damage  
   Boots: Max Mana, Raw Damage, Armour  
   Gloves: Raw Damage, % Critical Strike Damage, Armour  
   Bracers: Raw Damage, % Critical Strike Chance, Armour, % Mana Leech  
   Shoulders: Raw Damage, Armour, % Armour or Elemental Resistance

## **Rank 3 Ultimatum of Indisputed Speed**

This is where you unlock your first ultimatum and level it to rank 3 to meet one of the Adam Nostrus’ Trial 1 requirements. You will also upgrade your Elder Slorm capacity to 200+ in order to run the next part of the grind.  
In between runs, if your gear reaches full potential, reinforce it at Rick in town up to \+6.  
[Planner Snapshot](https://cayrac.github.io/slorm-_hWab_aaaPqbKbqtHbOYaaaaaaaIdWaaaEaaaabGka3aaaaaaaF4WarG8a)  
{% include embed/youtube.html id="hjBAYmWgGd4" %}  

1. Talk to Almerolis, select Battlefield, Wrath 1 and Battlefield Journey (Random and Everchanging Environment. Boss Events.).  
2. Enter, clear breaches until you can open the portal to the next floor (5 breaches below the number of breaches on the floor). Ignore normal monsters on the way between breaches, but do kill any elite you see for Elder Slorm. Once you can open the portal, go to the next floor right away. This saves lots of time as we can rush for the 30 Battlefield Bosses. Avoid chaos wave breaches, they take too long to complete, you can refer to the bottom of [this page]({% post_url blitzy/2025-05-14-G1B0000004 %}) for images on how to recognise breaches.  
   Elder Slorm drops from Elites in Battlefield. Repeat this until your Elder Slorm is full. Once it is full, exit the battlefield through the portal after killing the next battlefield boss.  
3. Olorin will appear, talk to him to unlock Slorm Temple.  
4. Talk to Almerolis, select The Slorm Temple.  
5. Enter and push as far as you can until you are out of Elder Slorm. At the end of each run, talk to Olorin, spend your Pure Slorm on upgrading Elder Slorm Max Capacity and dump the rest into Elder Slorm Find.  
   Note that Pure Slorm sometimes drop when triggering a room, there is no minimap icon so keep a lookout for it.  
6. Talk to Cory Ironbender to unlock The Great Forge.  
7. Repeat Battlefield and Slorm Temple until you have cleared Floor 20 of The Slorm Temple. Equip the ultimatum, talk to Olorin and upgrade this ultimatum to Rank 3\.

## **Activation & Effect Runes**

This is where you unlock the 2 runes needed for the build: Activation rune of Astorias, Thornbite (Effect) rune.  
This may be very grindy or fast depending on your luck, but none of the time spent is wasted. You are earning extra crafting materials, reapersmith spirits, goldus, slorm, skill masteries and gear potential while farming in the forge.  
Use the secondary skill slot to level skills to unlock access to all their upgrades, this will let you dump excess slorm into them for up to 3000 raw damage.  
In between runs, if your gear reaches full potential, reinforce it at Rick in town up to \+6.  
Use Kame’s Resolution for forge and Concentrated Ray for non-forge content. If you can’t be bothered to keep swapping, keep it on Kame’s.

2. Enter, open 2 gates only (again, to save elder slorm, open more gates if you want to).

   ![][image5]

   Do not pick any shadow related option, you cannot handle the shadow debuff yet.  
   Pick any Siege Leader Spawn chance option that appears.

1. Talk to Almerolis, select Netherworld, expand the map.  
   Clear as many cataclysmic expeditions and warlords as possible, hopefully finding the ungifted reaper if you have not.  
   Do not worry about not being able to clear certain warlords, you are not meant to be able to straight up clear everything the moment you start the third trial. There is no need to keep retrying runs that you cannot clear.  
   Once you are left with only the warlords that you cannot defeat, go to step 2\.  
   Tweaks to counter certain cataclysms:  
   * Reconstruction: Swap the last ancestral stone to fiery weapons. This will apply burn to enemies which deals damage every 0.5s to prevent them from healing.    Equip the primordial Ungifted reaper, and turn on all auras, you will have to swap the equipped skill on your ancestral hotkey bar to turn them all on.  
   This reaper grants way more damage, and removes the need for mana sustain. At this point we can fully rely on thornbite rune for ehp, we no longer need life sustain too. This means that we no longer need shadow resistance, freeing up the shadow resistance stat slots for all damage reduction.

   Equip the area damage reduction ultimatum.  
   You should be able to handle wrath 7 from the start, and very quickly up to wrath 9 after a few upgrades.  
   During these runs, prioritise elder slorm \> goldus \> war chest quantity \> war chest quality \> slormite \> equipment \> slormeline \> fragment \> astorias \> beigarth.  
   * Add legendary effects to your gear then reroll them to the correct legendary effect. There is no pity system for the reroll so it might take quite some grind to get the legendary effect you want. Craft for more legendary slormelines using rare and epic fragments/slormelines.  
     In order of priority:  
     1. Helmet: Slormandrite-Infused Diadem. More damage and defenses.  
     2. Chest: Chest of Immense Vitality. More damage and defenses.  
     3. Boots: Bulwark’s Resolve. More defenses.  
     4. Ring: Defender’s Twin Bands. More defenses.  
     5. Belt: Sahrusiel’s Pact. More defenses.  
     6. Amulet: Olorin’s Ultimate Enhancer. More movement speed or area damage reduction.  
     7. Bracers: Celestial Shackles or Ultrasonic Bracers. Either will work, we only want to lock more mana for more damage.  
     8. Gloves: Predator’s Fang. More damage.  
     9. Shoulders: Aiming Assistance Pads. More damage.  
     10. Cape: Soul Eating Mantle. More damage.  
     11. Ring: Ancestral Champions’ Present. Slightly more damage and defense.Reforge the legendary effects to max score. Use the reforge all scores option for cheaper cost.  
   * Reinforce all your gear to \+12  
   * Reach rank 15 enhancement rune of beigarth  
   * Reforge cory affinity into a total of \+50 astorias affinity on all your gear  
   * Reforge for the “after ungifted reaper” stats specified in [this section](#non-nether-gear-set)  
   * Optional: Reach 100 astorias affinity at cory ironbender, or as high as possible.  
4. Time to finish up the remaining cataclysmic expeditions and warlords. Equip your movement speed ultimatum and go ham.  
   Tweaks to counter certain cataclysms, you might have to use a combination of them for particularly nasty expeditions/warlords:  
   * Reconstruction: Swap the last ancestral stone to fiery weapons. This will apply burn to enemies which deals damage every 0.5s to prevent them from healing. If the possibly unintended interaction still exists, you can use the necrotic curse skill from the benediction reaper to one shot the boss if you wish to.  
   * Nullifying Shield: This is optional and to minimise annoyance only. Swap the last ancestral stone to electric overcharge. This will add 1 extra hit (dealing trash damage) to every hit by the clones, effectively halving the time spent to strip the block stacks of the enemies.  
   * AOE damage cataclysms: Swap to the area damage reduction ultimatum. This will give a only 3.5% more area damage reduction than what you already have.  
   * More defenses: For generic defenses, swap the last ancestral stone to risk of pain, if you do this, do not equip the area damage reduction ultimatum. For specific imbue resistance, use the search bar at the top and swap the last ancestral stone to them.  
   * More damage: Swap to the crit chance or crit damage ultimatum. Your damage is already pretty high, there should not be any need for this.  
   * Smaloron entry trick:  
     1. Swap to smaloron activation rune  
     2. Equip the trigger skill  
     3. Use the trigger skill  
     4. Swap back to astorias activation rune  
     5. Usually, once is enough to get going, and is still considered ethical.  
     6. Steps 1 to 3 can actually be repeated, which bypasses the cooldown of the trigger skill. **Repeating is unethical cheating, but I do it anyway** for particularly nasty cataclysms such as shadow clone. If you want to play ethically, farm for nether gear, [craft them](#basic-ungifted-nether-gear-set), reinforce them to \+15 and level them to 120, this is a long process. The other ethical way is to actually wait out the cooldown with spark machine and celestial decree turned off while still having Bryan’s Protection. If you are repeating for higher stacks up to your thornbite rune, use the enhancement rune of hagan while stacking and swap back to the enhancement rune of beigarth when you are done.  
   * Beigarth stacking trick: When you enter a new expedition, kill all monsters without triggering a breach, only trigger a breach at the end of each floor to enter the next floor. Repeat this until you have a comfortable number of stacks before starting to properly clear the expedition.  
   * Run through room clearing: Certain cataclysms leave behind lots of on death effects. You can consider clearing the room, running out and waiting for the on death effects to expire before returning to the room to clear the breach.  
   * Grenade room clearing: Kind of like how people chuck a grenade or flash bang through the door into the room before entering, you can do the same with your clones. Place clones into the next room without entering it, wait for a few seconds for things to clear before entering. This is easily done on keyboard and mouse, but is way harder if you are on a controller.  
5. Once you have cleared all the cataclysms and warlords, talk to Adam Nostrus.  
   This will unlock the final boss Ohm Agad.  
   Enter the fight at the castle doors.  
   Defeat Ohm Agad. This fight should be relatively easy  compared to certain warlords…  
   Use the movement speed ultimatum, activation rune of astorias, thornbite rune and enhancement rune of astorias.  
   Keep an eye on the life bar, when it reaches the cataclysm mark, it will remove all of your life, shield and thornbite protection. When that happens, rush to open all 6 breaches while dodging attacks, this will summon enemies for you to kill to trigger your thornbite rune for thornbite protection.  
   **CONGRATULATIONS FOR BEATING THE GAME\!\!\!**

## **Max Score Magic Find Set**Unedited yet, do not follow this section

In this section, you will be farming for pure stats and nether gear in the primordial netherworld to craft a triple max score pure stats magic find nether gear set.  
Planner Snapshot  
Playthrough Recording

1. Use the search bar at the top right in the expanded view. Hunt in the cataclysms expeditions that boosts the pure stat chance for the grafting feed you need. Repeat until your nether charge bar is full.  
2. Hunt primordial warlords for a full set of nether gear. Check their list of possible rewards when choosing a warlord to fight. For example, if you are looking for nether gloves, fight the warlord with the most number of gloves in their list of possible rewards.  
3. Repeat steps 3 and 4 until you have a full set of nether gear.  
4. Time to farm for pure stats for grafting. Only keep and use the max score pure stats, those with \!\!\! but aren’t max score can be discarded.  
   * Use the search bar at the top right in the expanded view. Hunt in the cataclysms expeditions that boosts the pure stat chance for the grafting feed you need. Repeat until the pure stat chance for the grafting feed you need appears at the hall of mimicking dead or the chamber of resurrected shadows.  
   * Now hunt in the hall or chamber while avoiding breaches. Only close a breach at the end of each floor to portal to the next floor. When you reach the breach limit, use the leave expedition key to exit. Repeat this until you have collected enough of the pure stats needed for grafting. This lets you farm in the densest map of the netherworld for the specific pure stat you want, maximising your efficiency.  
   * Repeat the above two steps for the other pure stats.  
5. Craft the max score magic find set. Farm the forge for crafting resources if you have to.  
   Reaper affinity, master and attributes are not required.  
6. After you are done crafting your max score magic find set, equip it.
